1
00:00:06,106 --> 00:00:08,708
♪

2
00:00:24,391 --> 00:00:26,259
(woman) HE’LL GET NIGHTMARES.

3
00:00:26,259 --> 00:00:28,695
(man) THE BOY HAS GOT TO HAVE A FEW NIGHTMARES TO GROW UP.

4
00:00:28,695 --> 00:00:30,597
JUST DON’T MAKE HIM STARE TOO LONG.

5
00:00:30,597 --> 00:00:32,298
IT COULD BE PSYCHOLOGICALLY DAMAGING AT HIS AGE.

6
00:00:32,298 --> 00:00:33,733
I WON’T. ZACH.

7
00:00:33,733 --> 00:00:35,869
I WON’T.

8
00:00:35,869 --> 00:00:37,504
COME HERE, BOY.

9
00:00:37,504 --> 00:00:39,506
SAY GOOD-BYE TO YOUR GRANDDADDY.

10
00:00:52,218 --> 00:00:53,753
SEE?

11
00:00:53,753 --> 00:00:55,588
THAT’S ENOUGH.

12
00:00:55,588 --> 00:00:57,123
SEE?

13
00:00:57,123 --> 00:01:00,093
THERE’S NOTHING TO BE AFRAID OF.

14
00:01:00,093 --> 00:01:02,662
YOUR GRANDDAD AIN’T EVEN THERE.

15
00:01:02,662 --> 00:01:04,097
THAT’S JUST HIS SHELL.

16
00:01:09,035 --> 00:01:10,537
LITTLE SPARTA,

17
00:01:10,537 --> 00:01:15,708
NOW, YOUR GRANDDADDY, HE ISN’T REALLY GONE, HONEY.

18
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:16,976
HE’S--HE’S WITH US.

19
00:01:16,976 --> 00:01:18,278
HE’S WITH US EVERYWHERE,

20
00:01:18,278 --> 00:01:20,079
ONLY HE DOESN’T HAVE THAT BIG OLD,

21
00:01:20,079 --> 00:01:22,515
HEAVY BODY TO CARRY AROUND ANYMORE.

22
00:01:22,515 --> 00:01:24,017
HE’S LIGHT NOW.

23
00:01:24,017 --> 00:01:27,053
YOU SEE, THAT’S WHAT HAPPENS WHEN PEOPLE DIE.

24
00:01:27,053 --> 00:01:29,522
THEY BECOME LIGHT ENOUGH TO GO TO HEAVEN.

25
00:01:29,522 --> 00:01:32,559
NOW, THAT’S NOTHING TO BE AFRAID OF, IS IT?

26
00:01:32,559 --> 00:01:34,194
NOW, GO ON, GO SEE YOUR AUNT CHARLOTTE.

27
00:01:34,194 --> 00:01:35,929
I KNOW SHE’S LOOKING FOR YOU.

28
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:44,103
[sighs]

29
00:01:49,209 --> 00:01:52,579
YEAH, I’D LIKE TO HAVE A CADILLAC LIKE YOURS.

30
00:01:52,579 --> 00:01:54,247
YOU GOT THAT BIG V-8 IN THERE?

31
00:01:54,247 --> 00:01:56,049
(woman) WE’VE BEEN DOING A LOT OF TRAVELING LATELY.

32
00:01:56,049 --> 00:01:58,952
[women speaking quietly]

33
00:01:58,952 --> 00:02:02,989
(Murtis) SPARTA, FORGIVE YOUR MURTIS.

34
00:02:02,989 --> 00:02:05,225
[sobbing]

35
00:02:08,094 --> 00:02:11,764
YOUR SWEET EAR, SPARTA.

36
00:02:11,764 --> 00:02:14,667
YOUR SWEET, SWEET EAR.

37
00:02:16,603 --> 00:02:20,206
WILL YOU FORGIVE YOUR SUGAR BUSH?

38
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:31,718
OH, MY.

39
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:34,554
I’LL GIVE THIS BACK TO YOU IN HEAVEN, SUGARCAKE.

40
00:02:34,554 --> 00:02:36,890
[man coughing]

41
00:02:36,890 --> 00:02:39,893
[conversations overlapping]

42
00:02:45,698 --> 00:02:47,300
(man) OH, NO.

43
00:02:47,300 --> 00:02:48,668
OF COURSE, I WOULD NEVER GET A CADDY WITHOUT LEATHER--

44
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:50,170
DAD.

45
00:02:50,170 --> 00:02:51,838
THOSE ARE LEATHER SEATS? OH, YES.

46
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:53,106
A CADDY WITHOUT LEATHER SEATS

47
00:02:53,106 --> 00:02:54,407
WOULD BE LIKE A GIRL WITHOUT A BEAU.

48
00:02:54,407 --> 00:02:57,877
DAD. LIKE TITS WITHOUT NIPPLES.

49
00:02:57,877 --> 00:02:59,512
DAD!

50
00:02:59,512 --> 00:03:00,880
LITTLE SPARTA,

51
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,649
COULD YOU BE QUIET FOR A WHILE?

52
00:03:02,649 --> 00:03:04,384
FUNERALS ARE A SOLEMN OCCASION,

53
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:05,685
AND YOU GOT TO SHUT UP SOMETIMES.

54
00:03:08,454 --> 00:03:09,556
[gasps]

55
00:03:12,091 --> 00:03:16,229
I WANT THE CASKET SEALED IMMEDIATELY.

56
00:03:16,229 --> 00:03:18,097
[Jerry Lee Lewis’ Down the Road a Piece]

57
00:03:32,779 --> 00:03:35,048
♪ WELL, IF YOU WANT TO HEAR SOME BOOGIE ♪

58
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:36,516
♪ LIKE I’M GONNA PLAY ♪

59
00:03:36,516 --> 00:03:37,951
♪ IT’S JUST AN OLD PIANO BARGE ♪

60
00:03:37,951 --> 00:03:39,519
IF IT TAKE THAT JOB IN NEW YORK,

61
00:03:39,519 --> 00:03:41,588
I’LL BE ABLE TO BUY YOU THAT CADDY YOU’VE ALWAYS WANTED.

62
00:03:41,588 --> 00:03:43,823
AW, SUGAR, I WISH YOU WOULDN’T DO THAT.

63
00:03:43,823 --> 00:03:46,659
[laughs]

64
00:03:46,659 --> 00:03:48,661
HOW ABOUT THAT, LITTLE SPARTA?

65
00:03:48,661 --> 00:03:51,531
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO HAVE A BIG OLD CADILLAC IN THE FAMILY?

66
00:03:53,499 --> 00:03:55,368
WHAT’S THE MATTER WITH HIM? IS HE SICK?

67
00:03:55,368 --> 00:03:56,936
NO...

68
00:03:56,936 --> 00:03:58,838
YOU TOLD HIM TO SHUT UP AT THE FUNERAL PARLOR,

69
00:03:58,838 --> 00:04:00,673
SO HE’S NOT TALKING.

70
00:04:00,673 --> 00:04:03,042
HE’S ANGRY WITH HIS FATHER.

71
00:04:03,042 --> 00:04:04,410
IT’S CALLED PASSIVE AGGRESSION.

72
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:05,945
IT’S WHAT CHILDREN DO NOWADAYS.

73
00:04:05,945 --> 00:04:07,480
OH, THEY DO, DO THEY? THEY DO.

74
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,683
WELL, THAT DOESN’T SOUND VERY AUDACIOUS TO ME.

75
00:04:10,683 --> 00:04:12,885
THAT’S WHAT WE’RE RAISING NOWADAYS,

76
00:04:12,885 --> 00:04:15,788
LITTLE SNIVELING, SPOILED, PASSIVE OFFSPRING

77
00:04:15,788 --> 00:04:17,757
AFRAID OF THEIR OWN SHADOWS.

78
00:04:17,757 --> 00:04:20,393
IF I WERE TO TRY THAT HOKEY0POKEY WITH MY DADDY, YOU KNOW WHAT HE’D SAY?

79
00:04:20,393 --> 00:04:21,861
ZACH, DON’T SAY IT.

80
00:04:21,861 --> 00:04:23,763
HE’D SAY, "YOU’D JUST BETTER SHARPEN UP,

81
00:04:23,763 --> 00:04:27,200
OR ELSE I’M GONNA HIT YOU SO HARD, YOU WON’T BE ABLE TO GET BACK UP AGAIN."

82
00:04:37,977 --> 00:04:40,246
OH, HELL, DID I JUST MISS THE TURNOFF TO MIRANDA’S?

83
00:04:40,246 --> 00:04:42,148
IT’S TWO MORE, ZACH.

84
00:04:42,148 --> 00:04:44,250
HEY, LITTLE SPARTA,

85
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:46,552
YOU REMEMBER YOUR AUNT MIRANDA, RIGHT, SPAR?

86
00:04:46,552 --> 00:04:47,920
ASK HER ABOUT INDIANS.

87
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:50,490
AUNT MIRANDA’S A BIG EXPERT ON INDIANS.

88
00:04:50,490 --> 00:04:52,825
YEAH, SHE’S A REAL EXPERT.

89
00:04:52,825 --> 00:04:54,627
(Zach) YOUR AUNT USED TO GET UP AND DANCE

90
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:56,996
IN THEM AUTHENTIC INDIAN POWWOWS.

91
00:04:59,432 --> 00:05:02,201
HOW ABOUT A WINK FOR THE CAMERA, MISS CHEROKEE QUEEN?

92
00:05:02,201 --> 00:05:04,737
(Zach) GOD, THEY JUST LOVED HER TO DEATH.

93
00:05:26,225 --> 00:05:28,027
[knock at door]

94
00:05:28,027 --> 00:05:29,729
(woman) MIRANDA?

95
00:05:29,729 --> 00:05:31,597
YEAH?

96
00:05:31,597 --> 00:05:33,933
YOUR FAMILY IS HERE, MIRANDA.

97
00:05:33,933 --> 00:05:36,002
Y’ALL COME ON IN. (Zach) THANK YOU.

98
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:39,238
MIRANDA, HONEY, YOU LOOK SO GOOD.

99
00:05:39,238 --> 00:05:41,841
I’D KISS YOU, BUT I SEE YOU GOT YOUR LIPS ALL GUSSIED UP.

100
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:43,309
(Miranda) OH, THAT’S OKAY, ZACHY.

101
00:05:45,845 --> 00:05:48,114
MM.

102
00:05:56,589 --> 00:05:57,857
DID YOU PACK YET?

103
00:05:57,857 --> 00:05:59,726
THREE DAYS AGO.

104
00:06:03,629 --> 00:06:06,599
(Zach) WHAT IN GOD’S NAME YOU GOT IN HERE, GIRL?

105
00:06:06,599 --> 00:06:08,034
YOU KNOW IT’S ONLY GONNA BE ONE NIGHT

106
00:06:08,034 --> 00:06:10,103
DADDY GOES IN THE GROUND TOMORROW.

107
00:06:10,103 --> 00:06:11,904
(Miranda) MAMA TELL YOU HOW IT HAPPENED?

108
00:06:11,904 --> 00:06:15,875
(Zach) HEART ATTACK, AND THEN HE PASSED ON A WEEK LATER.

109
00:06:15,875 --> 00:06:17,577
AND DON’T GO ASKING HER ABOUT PARTICULARS.

110
00:06:17,577 --> 00:06:19,145
SHE’S BEEN ACTING A LITTLE OFF-KILTER,

111
00:06:19,145 --> 00:06:20,446
AND I THINK IT WOULDN’T HURT

112
00:06:20,446 --> 00:06:21,814
TO GIVE HER SOME TIME TO SORT THINGS OUT

113
00:06:21,814 --> 00:06:22,915
BEFORE WE GO PRYING.

114
00:06:24,717 --> 00:06:27,019
WE GONNA SEE THE BODY FIRST?

115
00:06:27,019 --> 00:06:30,156
WELL, WE THOUGHT, TAKING INTO CONSIDERATION

116
00:06:30,156 --> 00:06:32,458
THE WAY THINGS WERE BETWEEN YOU AND OLD SPARTA,

117
00:06:32,458 --> 00:06:36,195
THAT YOU YOU’D SOON AS WELL SKIP THAT PART.

118
00:06:36,195 --> 00:06:37,930
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN NICE TO SEE HIM

119
00:06:37,930 --> 00:06:41,033
AT PEACE FOR A CHANGE.

120
00:06:41,033 --> 00:06:42,235
COME ON, WE GOT TO GO,

121
00:06:42,235 --> 00:06:43,770
OR ELSE THE BARBECUE’S GONNA GET COLD.

122
00:06:43,770 --> 00:06:45,238
LET’S GO.

123
00:06:45,238 --> 00:06:46,506
COME ON.

124
00:06:46,506 --> 00:06:47,874
(woman) ZACH, HOLD THOSE HORSES.

125
00:06:47,874 --> 00:06:49,642
LADIES.

126
00:06:49,642 --> 00:06:53,146
(Miranda) COME ON, LITTLE SPARTA, YOUR DAD’S IN A HURRY.

127
00:06:53,146 --> 00:06:54,914
[Zach grunting]

128
00:06:54,914 --> 00:06:57,350
WHY DON’T YOU SIT UP FRONT WITH THE ADULTS, MARY JOAN?

129
00:06:57,350 --> 00:07:00,520
SPARTA AND I WILL SIT IN BACK HERE.

130
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:03,823
[radio channels flipping]

131
00:07:03,823 --> 00:07:05,258
[man over radio] TEXANS ARE STILL IN SHOCK

132
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:06,459
OVER PRESIDENT JOHNSON’S ANNOUNCEMENT...

133
00:07:06,459 --> 00:07:08,594
I DECLARE A THUMB WAR.

134
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:10,163
[radio channels flipping]

135
00:07:10,163 --> 00:07:12,064
[Miranda laughing]

136
00:07:12,064 --> 00:07:13,800
[country and western music playing]

137
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,234
[gasps]

138
00:07:15,234 --> 00:07:18,538
OH, YOU GOT ME, SPAR.

139
00:07:18,538 --> 00:07:21,541
I REMEMBER WHEN I COULD ALWAYS BEAT YOU.

140
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:25,611
NOW YOU’RE PRACTICALLY A MAN.

141
00:07:25,611 --> 00:07:27,079
ZACH, IF YOU KEEP ON PLAYING WITH THAT RADIO,

142
00:07:27,079 --> 00:07:28,748
YOU’RE GONNA HAVE TO GET ME A ROOM

143
00:07:28,748 --> 00:07:30,183
AT THAT ASYLUM RIGHT NEXT TO MIRANDA’S.

144
00:07:30,183 --> 00:07:32,485
I’M JUST TRYING TO FIND YOU A GOOD STATION, SWEETIE.

145
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:35,021
GODDAMN, YOU’RE IMPATIENT.

146
00:07:35,021 --> 00:07:38,024
"GODDAMN"? IS THAT A WORD YOU WANT OUR LITTLE SPARTA TO BE SAYING?

147
00:07:38,024 --> 00:07:40,193
OUR SON DOESN’T TALK, REMEMBER?

148
00:07:40,193 --> 00:07:43,029
ISN’T THAT RIGHT, LITTLE SPARTA?

149
00:07:43,029 --> 00:07:44,997
SEE?

150
00:07:44,997 --> 00:07:48,367
WE GOT OURSELVES A LITTLE MUTE BOY.

151
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:50,436
IS THAT TRUE?

152
00:07:50,436 --> 00:07:52,839
YOU DON’T WANT TO TALK?

153
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:55,441
NOT EVEN TO ME?

154
00:07:55,441 --> 00:07:57,376
HERE WE GO.

155
00:07:57,376 --> 00:07:59,078
THANK THE LORD.

156
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,182
YOU’RE GONNA BE A REAL HEARTBREAKER

157
00:08:03,182 --> 00:08:04,784
WHEN YOU GROW UP-- YOU KNOW THAT, BOY?

158
00:08:04,784 --> 00:08:06,118
(Mary Joan) NOW, HE’S NOT, MIRANDA.

159
00:08:06,118 --> 00:08:07,720
HE’S GONNA BE A GENTLEMAN.

160
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,388
I’M RAISING LITTLE SPARTA

161
00:08:09,388 --> 00:08:11,691
TO JUST BE A GENTLEMAN.

162
00:08:11,691 --> 00:08:14,193
WELL, GENTLEMEN ARE THE WORST HEARTBREAKERS IN THE WORLD,

163
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:16,395
BECAUSE THEY JUST LOVE ONE WOMAN

164
00:08:16,395 --> 00:08:18,831
AND LEAVE THE OTHERS TO CRY THEMSELVES AWAY.

165
00:08:20,766 --> 00:08:23,402
HONEY, YOU GONNA SMOKE IN THE CAR?

166
00:08:23,402 --> 00:08:26,772
NO, I WAS GONNA ASK MY BROTHER, THE GENTLEMAN,

167
00:08:26,772 --> 00:08:29,141
IF HE WOULD STOP THE CAR SO A LADY COULD HAVE A SMOKE.

168
00:08:30,610 --> 00:08:34,447
♪ TEARDROPS FALL

169
00:08:34,447 --> 00:08:38,417
♪ LIKE RAINDROPS

170
00:08:38,417 --> 00:08:42,655
♪ WE MAKE MISTAKES

171
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:48,761
♪ AND FEEL SORRY

172
00:08:48,761 --> 00:08:51,864
♪ WHEN WE’VE MADE ♪

173
00:08:51,864 --> 00:08:58,337
♪ SOMEONE BLUE

174
00:08:58,337 --> 00:09:00,873
♪ BUT I’VE ♪

175
00:09:00,873 --> 00:09:04,343
♪ MADE THE GREATEST MISTAKE

176
00:09:04,343 --> 00:09:07,013
THERE’S CLINTON’S NEW CADILLAC.

177
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:09,015
AMAZING WHAT BLACK GOLD CAN BUY.

178
00:09:09,015 --> 00:09:11,484
ZACH, DON’T START WITH THE WHIT OIL SAGA AGAIN.

179
00:09:11,484 --> 00:09:13,252
WHAT IN GOD’S NAME IS MAMA CARRYING ON ABOUT?

180
00:09:13,252 --> 00:09:14,554
ZACH!

181
00:09:14,554 --> 00:09:17,156
ZACH, YOU’VE GOT HELP CLINTON WITH ROBERT E.

182
00:09:17,156 --> 00:09:19,392
HE’S GONE CRAZY.

183
00:09:19,392 --> 00:09:20,826
[woman shouting]

184
00:09:20,826 --> 00:09:22,461
HE’S GONNA KILL CLINTON.

185
00:09:22,461 --> 00:09:24,030
(Clinton) WHOA!

186
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:26,332
COME ON!

187
00:09:26,332 --> 00:09:28,568
[shouting]

188
00:09:28,568 --> 00:09:30,503
[camel growling]

189
00:09:30,503 --> 00:09:31,771
(Mary Joan) HONEY, BE CAREFUL, NOW.

190
00:09:31,771 --> 00:09:33,506
ALL RIGHT, COME ON, BOY.

191
00:09:33,506 --> 00:09:36,008
CALM DOWN, ROBERT E.

192
00:09:36,008 --> 00:09:37,076
[camel growling] GOD! GOD DAMN IT!

193
00:09:37,076 --> 00:09:38,244
(Zach) COME ON, BOY.

194
00:09:38,244 --> 00:09:40,212
STOP!

195
00:09:40,212 --> 00:09:42,448
JESUS, MARY AND JOSEPH! WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

196
00:10:15,648 --> 00:10:17,183
GOOD LORD, CLINTON.

197
00:10:17,183 --> 00:10:19,085
YOU COULD HAVE BEEN KILLED, HONEY.

198
00:10:19,085 --> 00:10:21,621
RIGHT BEFORE SPARTA DIED,

199
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:23,889
ROBERT E. STARTED ACTING KIND OF FUNNY.

200
00:10:23,889 --> 00:10:26,058
THERE YOU GO.

201
00:10:26,058 --> 00:10:27,960
YEAH.

202
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,997
HANK SAID HE’D BE BY LATER TO LOOK AT HIM.

203
00:10:30,997 --> 00:10:32,431
(man) MRS. WHIT?

204
00:10:32,431 --> 00:10:34,000
OH, THAT’S WALTER.

205
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,668
(Zach) WALTER?

206
00:10:35,668 --> 00:10:38,571
I THOUGHT HE WAS AWAY AT THAT COLORED MEDICAL SCHOOL.

207
00:10:38,571 --> 00:10:40,406
(Murtis) IT SEEMS HE DIDN’T HAVE ENOUGH MONEY

208
00:10:40,406 --> 00:10:42,108
TO FINISH THE YEAR, SO HE’S WORKING SOME.

209
00:10:42,108 --> 00:10:43,542
HELLO?

210
00:10:43,542 --> 00:10:46,579
MAYBE THE BOY CAN COME VISIT US, YOU KNOW, LATER.

211
00:10:46,579 --> 00:10:49,348
AFTER ALL, WITH DINNER AND THE READING OF THE WILL...

212
00:10:49,348 --> 00:10:53,419
BUT I INVITED HIM HERE BECAUSE OF THE WILL.

213
00:10:53,419 --> 00:10:55,421
MR. CRAWFORD SAYS HE’S IN IT.

214
00:10:55,421 --> 00:10:57,823
Y’ALL WIPE YOUR FEET OFF. Y’ALL WIPE YOUR FEET OFF.

215
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,492
COME ON IN.

216
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,626
HEY, WALTER.

217
00:11:00,626 --> 00:11:02,495
HEY, ZACH. HOW YOU DOING?

218
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,030
OH, I’M ALL RIGHT.

219
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,631
I’M REALLY SORRY TO HEAR ABOUT MR. WHIT.

220
00:11:05,631 --> 00:11:07,099
YEAH, I APPRECIATE YOU BEING HERE, THOUGH.

221
00:11:07,099 --> 00:11:09,101
COME ON IN. WHEN DID YOU GET BACK FROM SCHOOL?

222
00:11:09,101 --> 00:11:10,770
(Walter) OH, A COUPLE MONTHS AGO.

223
00:11:10,770 --> 00:11:12,671
BEEN DRIVING A BALER-- YOU WIPE YOUR FEET.

224
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:14,874
(Zach) BOY, THAT’S GOT TO BE ROUGH WITH ALL THAT HEAT WE GOT--

225
00:11:14,874 --> 00:11:16,542
[Clinton clears throat] WALTER, HOW ARE YOU?

226
00:11:16,542 --> 00:11:17,877
(Walter) OH, I’M DOING VERY WELL.

227
00:11:17,877 --> 00:11:19,912
THANK YOU, CLINTON.

228
00:11:19,912 --> 00:11:23,282
(Murtis) WALTER, YOU HAVE JUST GROWN INTO A MAN, HAVEN’T YOU?

229
00:11:23,282 --> 00:11:24,884
NEW YORK?

230
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:27,053
(Mary Joan) OH, YOU’VE BEEN TALKING TO ZACH.

231
00:11:27,053 --> 00:11:28,521
YEAH, BUT NEW YORK?

232
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:31,090
OF ALL THE PLACES.

233
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:34,093
I LOVE HIM, BUT HE DOESN’T HAVE A LICK OF SENSE IN HIS HEAD.

234
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:36,462
HE’S STUBBORN AS ALL GET-GO.

235
00:11:36,462 --> 00:11:38,531
EVEN WHEN HE WAS A CHILD,

236
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,132
YOU COULD TAKE A SWITCH TO ZACH,

237
00:11:40,132 --> 00:11:42,168
AND HE’D TURN RIGHT AROUND AND--

238
00:11:42,168 --> 00:11:44,303
AND JUST RAISE CAIN ALL OVER AGAIN.

239
00:11:44,303 --> 00:11:46,405
MURTIS, YOU KNOW I JUST IGNORE ZACH.

240
00:11:46,405 --> 00:11:49,341
OH! OH!

241
00:11:49,341 --> 00:11:50,743
ARE YOU OKAY?

242
00:11:50,743 --> 00:11:52,611
CHARLOTTE, I’M ALL RIGHT.

243
00:11:52,611 --> 00:11:53,979
ANYWAY, THE ONLY WAY

244
00:11:53,979 --> 00:11:55,448
WE’RE SEEING NEW YORK IS ON A TOUR BUS.

245
00:11:55,448 --> 00:11:57,316
I’VE DECIDED THAT. GOOD.

246
00:11:57,316 --> 00:11:59,785
YOU KNOW, THEY SAY THAT IN NEW YORK

247
00:11:59,785 --> 00:12:01,253
YOU CAN’T GO OUT AT NIGHT

248
00:12:01,253 --> 00:12:03,122
OR ELSE A NEGRO WILL JUMP OUT OF A SHADOW

249
00:12:03,122 --> 00:12:04,690
AND SHOOT YOU WITH A BIG OLD GUN.

250
00:12:04,690 --> 00:12:06,692
YOU KNOW, CHARLOTTE, I DON’T BELIEVE THAT’S TRUE.

251
00:12:06,692 --> 00:12:08,594
WELL, CLINTON TOLD ME SO.

252
00:12:08,594 --> 00:12:11,664
OOOH, THAT PECAN PIE LOOKS LOVELY. HA HA!

253
00:12:11,664 --> 00:12:13,399
THANK YOU.

254
00:12:13,399 --> 00:12:15,468
OH, I DIDN’T KNOW WE WERE SUPPOSED TO BRING DESSERT.

255
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:18,370
WE WEREN’T. I JUST DID IT LAST MINUTE.

256
00:12:18,370 --> 00:12:19,905
(Charlotte) WELL, IF I’D HAVE KNOWN, I WOULD’VE BROUGHT MY MOUSSE.

257
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:21,874
IT’S A THREE-CHOCOLATE MOUSSE.

258
00:12:21,874 --> 00:12:24,276
WELL, HONEY, YOU JUST BRING IT NEXT TIME.

259
00:12:24,276 --> 00:12:25,811
Y’ALL NEED ANY HELP?

260
00:12:25,811 --> 00:12:27,646
OH, NO, WE GOT IT COVERED.

261
00:12:29,515 --> 00:12:32,151
HAVE YOU HAD YOUR MEDICATION?

262
00:12:33,652 --> 00:12:36,589
TWICE, SO I’D BE DOUBLY SANE TONIGHT.

263
00:12:38,724 --> 00:12:41,460
HONEY, PLEASE DON’T-- DON’T DO THAT IN HERE.

264
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:43,762
IT’S SO NICE, AND IT SMELLS LIKE PIE.

265
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:51,637
(Clinton) POWER WINDOWS, LEATHER UPHOLSTERY,

266
00:12:51,637 --> 00:12:54,073
THAT’S ALL WELL AND GOOD. THAT WILL PLEASE THE MISSUS.

267
00:12:54,073 --> 00:12:55,975
SHE WEREN’T BORN WITH MUCH, BLESS HER HEART,

268
00:12:55,975 --> 00:12:57,676
BUT SHE SURE HAS A TASTE FOR FINER THINGS.

269
00:12:57,676 --> 00:12:59,945
I TOLD HER, "YOU LISTEN..."

270
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:04,316
NOW, YOU CLIMB ON IN THERE AND SIT IN THAT BUCKET SEAT.

271
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:06,919
HUH? GOOD?

272
00:13:06,919 --> 00:13:08,988
IT’S NICE.

273
00:13:08,988 --> 00:13:10,589
(Clinton) YOU LIKE WHAT YOU SEE, WALTER?

274
00:13:10,589 --> 00:13:12,424
I SURE DO.

275
00:13:12,424 --> 00:13:13,859
WHAT’S THE MOST EXPENSIVE VEHICLE YOU’VE EVER DRIVEN IN?

276
00:13:13,859 --> 00:13:16,662
M48 TANK, CREW TWO, SOUTH SAIGON. [laughs]

277
00:13:16,662 --> 00:13:18,330
[camel bellowing]

278
00:13:18,330 --> 00:13:21,000
YOU KNOW, YOU OUGHT TO GET YOURSELF ONE OF THESE, ZACH.

279
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:23,602
THEY’RE NOT THAT EXPENSIVE IF YOU DON’T GET ONE

280
00:13:23,602 --> 00:13:25,938
WITH ALL THE DOODADS IN THEM LIKE I HAVE.

281
00:13:25,938 --> 00:13:28,007
WELL, MARY JOAN’S BEEN AFTER ME

282
00:13:28,007 --> 00:13:29,808
SINCE I-CAN’T-REMEMBER TO GET HER ONE.

283
00:13:29,808 --> 00:13:32,444
I PROMISED HER, IF I TAKE THAT JOB UP IN NEW YORK, I’D SEE ABOUT IT.

284
00:13:32,444 --> 00:13:33,712
(Clinton) NEW YORK?

285
00:13:33,712 --> 00:13:35,714
THAT SEEMS LIKE THE END OF THE EARTH.

286
00:13:35,714 --> 00:13:37,216
ARE YOU SERIOUSLY CONSIDERING THAT?

287
00:13:37,216 --> 00:13:39,919
THERE’S A LOT OF OPPORTUNITY THERE.

288
00:13:39,919 --> 00:13:41,487
WELL, THAT COULD BE A GOOD PLAY, THOUGH--

289
00:13:41,487 --> 00:13:43,122
YOU GO UP NORTH AND WORK A COUPLE OF YEARS

290
00:13:43,122 --> 00:13:44,990
AND COME BACK HOME WITH A BETTER RESUME.

291
00:13:44,990 --> 00:13:48,394
YEAH, SOMETHING LIKE THAT.

292
00:13:48,394 --> 00:13:50,196
I FIGURE WE’D MAKE SOME MONEY

293
00:13:50,196 --> 00:13:52,665
AND MAYBE SET A LITTLE BIT ASIDE,

294
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:54,400
NOT LIKE YOU AND CHARLOTTE, OF COURSE,

295
00:13:54,400 --> 00:13:56,268
BUT ENOUGH THAT I CAN INVEST A BIT IN THE STOCK MARKET.

296
00:13:56,268 --> 00:13:58,037
STOCK MARKET? I WOULDN’T MESS WITH THAT.

297
00:13:58,037 --> 00:13:59,538
IT’S AN AWFUL BAD TIME.

298
00:13:59,538 --> 00:14:01,740
YOU KNOW, THERE ARE A LOT OF SMART FELLAS

299
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:03,709
WHO HAVE BEEN LOSING THEIR SHIRTS.

300
00:14:03,709 --> 00:14:05,644
IF I WERE YOU, I’D JUST, YOU KNOW, HOLD ON TO WHAT YOU GOT.

301
00:14:05,644 --> 00:14:07,346
YEAH, WELL, IF YOU DON’T RISK IT,

302
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:08,914
YOU DON’T DRINK CHAMPAGNE.

303
00:14:08,914 --> 00:14:10,583
AND WHAT IF YOU’RE DADDY HADN’T RISKED DRILLING

304
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,084
THAT OIL WELL OUT THERE?

305
00:14:12,084 --> 00:14:13,452
YOU KNOW, I’M GONNA TELL YOU SOMETHING.

306
00:14:13,452 --> 00:14:15,688
MONEY IS A FUNNY THING, ZACH.

307
00:14:15,688 --> 00:14:17,623
NOW, THERE’S SOME FELLAS, THEY’LL SPIT ON A SEED,

308
00:14:17,623 --> 00:14:21,060
THEY’LL GROW A FOREST, AND THEN YOU GOT OTHER FELLAS,

309
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:23,963
THEY’LL TURN A GARDEN OF EDEN INTO A DESERT.

310
00:14:26,765 --> 00:14:29,201
YEAH, I RECKON SO.

311
00:14:44,650 --> 00:14:47,653
[faint eerie noises]

312
00:14:53,826 --> 00:14:55,728
[breathing deeply]

313
00:15:16,015 --> 00:15:18,951
[rattling noise]

314
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:26,158
[thunder booming]

315
00:15:30,863 --> 00:15:32,498
(man) I’VE JUST GOT SOME UNFINISHED BUSINESS

316
00:15:32,498 --> 00:15:34,633
I’VE GOT TO LOOK AFTER HERE.

317
00:15:34,633 --> 00:15:36,702
JUST HANG ON, NOW.

318
00:15:36,702 --> 00:15:38,504
HI.

319
00:15:38,504 --> 00:15:40,205
[laughs] YOU DIDN’T THINK I’D LEAVE

320
00:15:40,205 --> 00:15:42,207
WITHOUT SAYING GOOD-BYE, DID YOU?

321
00:15:42,207 --> 00:15:44,576
YOU KNOW YOUR OLD GRANDPA BETTER THAN THAT.

322
00:15:44,576 --> 00:15:48,013
YOU LOOK NONE THE WORSE SINCE I LEFT.

323
00:15:48,013 --> 00:15:50,282
WISH I COULD SAY THE SAME FOR OLD ROBERT E.

324
00:15:51,617 --> 00:15:54,453
COME ON OVER HERE, WILL YA?

325
00:15:54,453 --> 00:15:56,722
THAT’S MY BOY.

326
00:15:56,722 --> 00:15:57,990
[laughs]

327
00:15:57,990 --> 00:16:00,426
ARE YOU SURPRISED TO SEE ME?

328
00:16:00,426 --> 00:16:02,661
WELL, I’M FULL OF SURPRISES.

329
00:16:02,661 --> 00:16:04,396
LET’S GET STARTED.

330
00:16:04,396 --> 00:16:07,399
THERE’S SOME OLD FELLAS UPSTAIRS CHOMPIN’ AT THE BIT TO MEET YOU.

331
00:16:09,001 --> 00:16:11,070
UP WE GO, COME ON.

332
00:16:14,173 --> 00:16:16,709
DAMN IT TO HELL!

333
00:16:18,777 --> 00:16:20,813
SORRY FOR MY LANGUAGE, BOY.

334
00:16:20,813 --> 00:16:24,149
I JUST WISH YOUR GRANDMOTHER WOULD STOP MESSIN’ WITH MY EAR.

335
00:16:24,149 --> 00:16:25,484
COME ON.

336
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:28,020
(man #1) THAT’S TEN, GRANDDAD.

337
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:29,755
TELL HIM, DADDY.

338
00:16:29,755 --> 00:16:31,890
(man #2) YOU CAN’T PUT THAT DOWN THERE; TAKE THAT BACK.

339
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:32,925
I SURE CAN. WHY CAN’T HE?

340
00:16:32,925 --> 00:16:35,794
WHY--TELL HIM, DAD.

341
00:16:35,794 --> 00:16:37,496
POP, YOU-- YOU TAUGHT HIM.

342
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,131
(man #2) YEAH, I TAUGHT HIM,

343
00:16:39,131 --> 00:16:41,100
BUT I DIDN’T TEACH HIM TO CHEAT LIKE THAT, YOU KNOW?

344
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:43,235
AND LIKE I’M GONNA PLAY THIS DOUBLE DEUCE RIGHT THERE.

345
00:16:43,235 --> 00:16:45,003
[laughs]

346
00:16:45,003 --> 00:16:46,939
WHOA, HE DOES IT TO US EVERY TIME.

347
00:16:46,939 --> 00:16:48,741
THERE HE IS. THERE IS OUR BOY.

348
00:16:48,741 --> 00:16:50,909
(man #2) THAT’S OUR BOY.

349
00:16:50,909 --> 00:16:52,745
LITTLE SPARTA,

350
00:16:52,745 --> 00:16:56,415
THIS HERE IS YOUR GREAT-GREAT-GREAT- GRANDDADDY, LUCAS,

351
00:16:56,415 --> 00:16:58,450
SHAKE IS HAND.

352
00:16:58,450 --> 00:16:59,918
ENCHANTE.

353
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:04,256
BOY, HE’S GOT A GRIP.

354
00:17:04,256 --> 00:17:06,592
HE’S GOT A GRIP AS GOOD AS MINE, BOYS.

355
00:17:06,592 --> 00:17:09,161
[laughter]

356
00:17:09,161 --> 00:17:11,330
UH, GRANDDADDY... UH-HUH?

357
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:12,931
YOU WANT TO INTRODUCE US?

358
00:17:12,931 --> 00:17:14,666
YEAH, I GUESS SO.

359
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,669
THIS MAMA’S BOY HERE ALL DRESSED UP PRETTY

360
00:17:17,669 --> 00:17:19,438
LIKE HE’S GOING TO SUNDAY CHURCH,

361
00:17:19,438 --> 00:17:23,308
THAT’S YOUR GREAT-GRANDDADDY, ACHILLES.

362
00:17:23,308 --> 00:17:25,277
NOW, HE’S THE POLITICIAN IN THE FAMILY.

363
00:17:25,277 --> 00:17:29,248
AND THIS IS YOUR GREAT-GREAT GRANDDADDY,

364
00:17:29,248 --> 00:17:30,949
JEFFERSON,

365
00:17:30,949 --> 00:17:34,153
HE’S JUST UGLY.

366
00:17:34,153 --> 00:17:36,155
(Sparta) GRANDDADDY LUCAS WAS THE FIRST WHIT

367
00:17:36,155 --> 00:17:38,424
IN THE STATE OF TEXAS. THAT’S RIGHT.

368
00:17:38,424 --> 00:17:39,992
HE WAS ALSO THE FIRST WHIT TO RECOGNIZE

369
00:17:39,992 --> 00:17:42,027
THE AWESOME MILITARY POTENTIAL OF THE DROMEDARY.

370
00:17:42,027 --> 00:17:45,164
I WISH YOU WOULD STOP GABBING LIKE A WOMAN.

371
00:17:45,164 --> 00:17:48,000
IT’S MY STORY. LET ME TELL THE BOY.

372
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,902
YES, SIR.

373
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:51,503
ALL RIGHT,

374
00:17:51,503 --> 00:17:53,405
THIS IS HANNIBAL.

375
00:17:53,405 --> 00:17:55,240
HE’S THE FIRST CAMEL IN THE WHIT CLAN,

376
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:56,909
NOW, I GOT HIM

377
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,578
WHEN I WAS ACTING AS A SPY

378
00:17:59,578 --> 00:18:02,448
DURING THE YANKEE INVASION.

379
00:18:02,448 --> 00:18:06,452
FOR DAYS, I’D BEEN WANDERING THE DESERT

380
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:08,520
WITHOUT FOOD OR WATER.

381
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:11,390
MY HORSE HAD UP AND DIED OF THIRST,

382
00:18:11,390 --> 00:18:15,594
SO I FILLED MY CANTEEN WITH HER BLOOD TO KEEP MYSELF

383
00:18:15,594 --> 00:18:19,965
FROM SUFFERING THE SAME FATE.

384
00:18:19,965 --> 00:18:23,202
I’D JUST ABOUT GIVEN UP THE GHOST

385
00:18:23,202 --> 00:18:27,306
WHEN I STUMBLED UPON AN HONEST-TO-GOD MIRACLE...

386
00:18:27,306 --> 00:18:28,841
[men laughing]

387
00:18:30,476 --> 00:18:34,112
CAMELS BROUGHT FROM THE HOLY LAND BY THE YANKS

388
00:18:34,112 --> 00:18:36,248
TO HELP MOVE SUPPLIES.

389
00:18:36,248 --> 00:18:37,983
AND WHEN I SAW HANNIBAL STANDING THERE,

390
00:18:37,983 --> 00:18:42,421
AHHH, I KNEW GOD HISSELF HAD SENT ME THE ANSWER

391
00:18:42,421 --> 00:18:45,290
TO MY PRAYERS.

392
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:46,925
[gunshot] AAH!

393
00:18:46,925 --> 00:18:48,794
YAAAA-HOO!

394
00:18:48,794 --> 00:18:51,563
[men screaming and gunshots firing]

395
00:18:58,637 --> 00:19:01,206
AHHHHHHH-HA-HA-HA-HA!

396
00:19:01,206 --> 00:19:02,574
[gunshots]

397
00:19:02,574 --> 00:19:04,409
WHOOOOO!

398
00:19:04,409 --> 00:19:06,645
♪

399
00:19:17,723 --> 00:19:19,224
YOU SEE,

400
00:19:19,224 --> 00:19:22,094
THE MINUTE I LAID EYES ON THEM CRITTERS,

401
00:19:22,094 --> 00:19:25,664
I KNEW THAT THE CAMEL WAS THE DESERT WARRIOR’S STEED.

402
00:19:30,802 --> 00:19:33,472
(man) COMPANY HALT!

403
00:19:33,472 --> 00:19:35,374
HOLD YOUR POSITIONS!

404
00:19:37,776 --> 00:19:40,045
[men hooting and laughing]

405
00:19:40,045 --> 00:19:42,781
YANKEES.

406
00:19:42,781 --> 00:19:44,316
HERE WE GO, BOYS.

407
00:19:44,316 --> 00:19:45,584
CHARGE!

408
00:19:45,584 --> 00:19:46,652
YAAAAA!

409
00:19:46,652 --> 00:19:47,920
CHARGE!

410
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,221
COME ON, CAMEL!

411
00:19:49,221 --> 00:19:50,422
CHARGE!

412
00:19:50,422 --> 00:19:51,590
HEY!

413
00:19:51,590 --> 00:19:52,891
LET’S GET THEM, BOY; LET’S GET--

414
00:19:52,891 --> 00:19:54,426
COME ON, YOU, CHARGE; GET THEM, NOW!

415
00:19:54,426 --> 00:19:55,594
COME ON, LET’S GET THEM!

416
00:19:55,594 --> 00:19:57,162
LET’S KILL SOME YANKEE, BOY!

417
00:19:57,162 --> 00:19:58,564
CAPTAIN WHIT.

418
00:19:58,564 --> 00:19:59,498
WHAT?

419
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:02,935
THE ENEMY IS LAUGHING AT US, SIR.

420
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:05,037
(man) ARE YOU GONNA CHARGE OR NOT?

421
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:06,939
(Lucas) COME BACK HERE!

422
00:20:06,939 --> 00:20:08,840
I’LL KILL YA!

423
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:10,242
CHARGE!

424
00:20:10,242 --> 00:20:14,179
COME ON! COME HERE, YOU SONS OF BITCHES!

425
00:20:14,179 --> 00:20:16,148
COME BACK AND FIGHT!

426
00:20:21,653 --> 00:20:22,988
I LOST.

427
00:20:24,957 --> 00:20:27,359
[camel grunting] SHIT.

428
00:20:27,359 --> 00:20:30,662
SHIT! SHIT!

429
00:20:35,300 --> 00:20:38,103
HANNIBAL, DID YOU SEE THAT?

430
00:20:38,103 --> 00:20:39,671
THEY ARE LAUGHING AT US...

431
00:20:39,671 --> 00:20:40,806
LAUGHING. CAPTAIN WHIT.

432
00:20:40,806 --> 00:20:41,873
[growling]

433
00:20:41,873 --> 00:20:43,141
[spits]

434
00:20:43,141 --> 00:20:44,776
DON’T YOU SPIT AT ME. YOU SPIT AT ME?

435
00:20:44,776 --> 00:20:45,777
[spits]

436
00:20:45,777 --> 00:20:47,946
CAPTAIN WHIT. WHAT?

437
00:20:47,946 --> 00:20:50,048
YOU SHOULDN’T REALLY BLAME YOURSELF, SIR.

438
00:20:50,048 --> 00:20:52,718
MAYBE THE CAMEL ISN’T THE DESERT WARRIOR’S STEED.

439
00:20:56,788 --> 00:21:02,127
THERE IS NOTHING WRONG WITH THE DESERT WARRIOR’S STEED!

440
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:04,963
WE JUST HAD A BAD DAY, THAT’S ALL.

441
00:21:04,963 --> 00:21:07,833
THE CAMEL CAVALRY DISTINGUISHED ITSELF IN BATTLE,

442
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:09,301
REPELLING THE NORTHERN ATTACK

443
00:21:09,301 --> 00:21:12,771
WITH ONLY ONE CASUALTY AMONG THE MEN.

444
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:17,976
AFTER THE WAR, I RAISED

445
00:21:17,976 --> 00:21:20,379
A WHOLE MESS OF CAMELS,

446
00:21:20,379 --> 00:21:25,550
BUT THE AUTOMOBILE KILLED OFF THE CAMEL TRAFFIC IN TEXAS.

447
00:21:25,550 --> 00:21:28,420
ROBERT E. IS THE LAST.

448
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:34,259
HE’S THE LAST OF THE WHIT DESERT WARRIOR STEEDS.

449
00:21:34,259 --> 00:21:35,794
(Mary Joan) LITTLE SPARTA, YOU WANT TO COME ON IN THE HOUSE NOW?

450
00:21:35,794 --> 00:21:37,429
IT’S TIME FOR SUPPER.

451
00:21:39,431 --> 00:21:40,999
YOU STILL AIN’T TALKING, HUH?

452
00:21:40,999 --> 00:21:42,134
WELL, COME ON.

453
00:21:42,134 --> 00:21:44,002
HEY, WHAT DID I SAY, LITTLE MAN?

454
00:21:44,002 --> 00:21:45,771
[chair squeaks]

455
00:21:45,771 --> 00:21:47,139
HEY.

456
00:21:47,139 --> 00:21:49,741
DON’T TELL ME YOU’RE DEAF NOW, TOO.

457
00:21:52,411 --> 00:21:54,813
[sobbing]

458
00:22:09,027 --> 00:22:10,962
IT’S RIB-TIME, EVERYBODY.

459
00:22:10,962 --> 00:22:13,331
OH, OKAY.

460
00:22:20,272 --> 00:22:22,207
(Clinton) PASS ME ANOTHER DR. PEPPER DOWN HERE.

461
00:22:22,207 --> 00:22:24,509
(Zach) HEY, MOM, YOU NEED SOME HELP WITH THEM RIBS?

462
00:22:24,509 --> 00:22:27,512
OH, HERE SHE COMES. OH, MY...

463
00:22:27,512 --> 00:22:29,147
ENJOY ’EM.

464
00:22:29,147 --> 00:22:32,217
THIS IS THE LAST OF SPARTA’S BARBECUE SAUCE.

465
00:22:32,217 --> 00:22:33,685
WHAT YOU MEAN BY THAT?

466
00:22:33,685 --> 00:22:35,220
(Murtis) I MEAN...

467
00:22:35,220 --> 00:22:36,755
THE RECIPE WAS IN HIS HEAD,

468
00:22:36,755 --> 00:22:39,124
AND HE’S TAKING THAT TO THE GRAVE, NOW, HASN’T HE?

469
00:22:39,124 --> 00:22:42,227
WELL, NOW, THAT’S A GENUINE TRAGEDY. WELL, YES, IT IS.

470
00:22:42,227 --> 00:22:44,730
MAMA, SIT DOWN HERE AND ENJOY YOUR SUPPER.

471
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:46,932
(Mary Joan) LITTLE SPARTA, YOU HAVE SOME OF THOSE RIBS.

472
00:22:46,932 --> 00:22:48,467
DEAR LORD,

473
00:22:48,467 --> 00:22:50,535
WE THANK THEE

474
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:52,437
FOR THE JOY THAT YOU HAVE BROUGHT US

475
00:22:52,437 --> 00:22:56,475
AND FOR THE WARMTH AND LOVE OF THIS FAMILY REUNION

476
00:22:56,475 --> 00:22:59,778
ON THIS MOST SORROWFUL OCCASION OF OUR LOVED ONE’S DEATH.

477
00:22:59,778 --> 00:23:03,982
WE PRAY THAT GRANDFATHER SPARTA

478
00:23:03,982 --> 00:23:06,384
HAS REACHED HIS REWARD IN HEAVEN

479
